#HELPS

-1 DROW DARK-ELF~
Dark-elves are an offshoot of the normal breed of elves. They are similar 
in most ways, save their skin color is black, or deep purple, and their hair 
color is generally white, or silver. They usually have magenta, or amber 
eyes, and they are amazingly smart, and nimble, making excellent thieves, 
mages, and ninjas. Dark-elves generally hate the elves that drove them 
below the surface of the world, and take revenge when possible.

Starting stats:    Str: 11 Int: 17 Wis: 14 Dex: 16 Con: 13
Maximum stats: Str: 20 Int: 25 Wis: 23 Dex: 25 Con: 22

Resist: magic
Vulnerable: light

Special skill: Dual wield %100
~

-1 CYBORG~
A hybrid of Man and Machine, a cyborg is an organism that can either be
half man half machine, or any other combination, right down to a machine 
with human tissue, like a Terminator. There is no uniform type, but most 
may be considered to be humanoid in form, and more than human, in at 
least some way.

Starting stats:    Str: 15 Int: 18 Wis: 16 Dex: 14 Con: 14 
Maximum Stats: Str: 24 Int: 24 Wis: 25 Dex: 23 Con: 23

Resist: Charm, Weapon
Vulnerable: Fire, Cold

Special Skill: Optic Blast %100
~

-1 Elf HIGH-ELF~
Elves are tall, and thin, with hair colors ranging from light green, to near  
black. Their eyes are frequently pale blues and greens. Elves are masters 
of magic, and excel at the arts of both the Cleric, and Mage. Elves are 
known for arrogance, and frivolity, for their love of nature, and 
their charisma. They are said to be charming, captivating, and beautiful.

Starting stats:    Str: 10 Int: 17 Wis: 14 Dex: 15 Con: 13
Maximum stats: Str: 19 Int: 25 Wis: 23 Dex: 24 Con: 22 

Resist: Charm, Magic
Vulnerable: Fire

Special Skills: Infrared, Regeration %100
~

-1 VAMPIRE~
Fiends of the night, legendary stalkers of humans, and feeders of blood, 
this creatures are frequently beautiful, and seductive on the outside, yet
evil and predatory in reality. They drain the blood of the living to sustain
their undead lives, and make excellent members of each of the classes. 
They are immune to poisons,and the elements, while succumbing more 
often to the effects of holy items, and sunlight.  It is rumoured that a stake 
to the heart will kill a creature permanently.

Starting stats:    Str: 16 Int: 15 Wis: 15 Dex: 14 Con: 14
Maximum stats: Str: 25 Int: 23 Wis: 24 Dex: 23 Con: 23

Immune: cold lightning poison
Resist: charm
Vulnerable: holy light

Special skills: Drain, Feed %100
~

-1 HUMAN~
The most basic of races, if you dont know what a human is, perhaps a 
good look in the mirror is in order? The primary advantages of humans, 
concern the possibility that they might be Espers, or Demons, in 
disguise, and that eq is more effective when worn by a human.
	
Starting stats:    Str: 13 Int: 14 Wis: 13 Dex: 13 Con: 13
Maximum stats: Str: 23 Int: 23 Wis: 23 Dex: 23 Con: 23

Resist: None
Vulnerabilities: None

Special Skill: Can become Espers, Demons
SEE ALSO: Help HOWTOESPER, Help HOWTODEMON
~

-1 ESPER~ Creatures made entirely of Magic, and devoted to good, they are
the masters of the use of magic, and are unparalled in the realms of
intellectual and magical study and pursuit. They make the best possible
Clerics, Mages, and Monks, and are formidable foes. They are allied with
all those who fight for the cause of good. Like demons, they too often
begin life believing themselves to be human, and only later does their
true nature emerge, a being of immense power. 

Starting stats:    Str: 15 Int: 16 Wis: 15 Dex: 15 Con: 15
Maximum stats: Str: 20 Int: 25 Wis: 25 Dex: 25 Con: 22 

Immune: light
Resist: magic 
Vulnerability: negative

Special Skills: Spells do 2x damage, double mana gain, spells cost 0.5x to cast.
SEE ALSO: Help HOWTOESPER
~

-1 DEMON~
Creatures of vast and limitless evil, this form of demon is often the result 
of either a Succubus, or an Incubus, mating with a human. The result is 
frequently an otherworldly demon, of great power. Resistant to damage 
like none other, they are resilient as well as deadly, wielding deadly
hellfire, they make truly terrifying foes. They spend much of their early 
lives living as humans, frequently not manifesting the true horror of
their beings until later.  

Starting stats:    Str: 15 Int: 16 Wis: 15 Dex: 15 Con: 15
Maximum Stats: Str: 25 Int: 20 Wis: 22 Dex: 25 Con: 25

Immune: charm
Resist: weapon
Vulnerable: holy

Special Skills:Gain double hit points each level, Hellbender %1, Possess Person %100
SEE ALSO: Help HOWTODEMON
~

-1 DRAGON DRAGON-KIN~
The Ancestors of mighty dragons, and powerful in their own right, they 
have mighty wings they use to fly, and superior intellect, wisdom, 
strength, fortitude, and agility. They make excellent members of all 
classes, and many forms of weapons are ineffective against their tough 
scales. Dragon-kin come in nearly as many colours as do Dragons, and 
share many common features with them, tails, wings, claws, and 
multitudes of of sharp teeth in their maws.

Starting stats:    Str: 16  Int: 17 Wis: 16 Dex: 16 Con: 16
Maximum stats: Str: 25  Int: 25 Wis: 25 Dex: 25 Con: 25

Resist: charm slashing
Vulnerable: none

Special Skills: Flight
~

-1 GIANT~
Huge and brutal, and frequently known to live in less than civilized 
conditions, Giants are known for their vast physical power, and not so 
fast speed, both of thought, and movement. The make excellent Warriors, 
but arent well suited for the more nimble, nor for the more intellectual 
classes. Giants have been known to kidnap and eat, or enslave humans, 
generally female humans. They are also gifted with the ability to throw 
massive rocks at their enemies...or to throw their enemies!

Starting stats:    Str: 16 Int: 12 Wis: 13 Dex: 12 Con: 14
Maximum stats: Str: 25 Int: 20 Wis: 22 Dex: 20 Con: 23

Resist: None
Vulnerabilty: None

Special: Throw %100
~

-1 DWARF~
Short, underground dwellers, usually possessed of a paunch, short 
stature, and a mighty beard, they are master craftsmen, making many of
the most powerful items, and making many powerful items more so. They 
make excellent warriors and clerics, and their stamina is unparalled. 
Dwarves are sometimes friends with elves, who they consider somewhat 
frivolous, and sometimes disdainful of them, due to their own dour 
dispositions. A dwarf can always be counted upon to drink copious 
amounts of alcohol, fight as often as possible, and work in a forge, 
whenever not doing the other two. 

Starting stats:    Str: 16 Int: 12 Wis: 14 Dex: 9   Con: 16
Maximum stats: Str: 25 Int: 20 Wis: 23 Dex: 18 Con: 25

Resist: magic
Vulnerability: None

Special Skill: Forge %100
~

