-1 DEAD 'DEAD FLAG'~
The dead flag is another insentive to choose the path of a killer. Unlike
other muds, when you die..there is a possiblity that someone 'other than
the first killer' to kill you. This is very frustrating especially when
you are trying to re-equip yourself after been looted. The flag is designed
to deter those that like to either: Kill players after they have just died
from a pk battle, or those that like to multi-kill(illegal). When you die
from another player, your character will be flagged (`8DEAD``). Any player
flagged will not be able to be pkilled until one of two things happen:

1) The character raises a level.
2) The character quits the game.

Once either of these two things happen, the flag will be removed from the
player, and can be pkilled again. The main purpose is to deter multi-killing
which means that re-equiping yourself without being pkilled is an added plus.
There is only one stipulation to this flag which is that characters already
flagged (KILLER) will NOT recieve the flag if they are pkilled.
~

-1 HOWTOESPER~
Because the outer and inner realms are slowly being connect, the Espers
have found ways to live with the mortal humans on the planet. Esper, beings
made from the essance of magick, have found ways to create a being physically
like a human. Because the humans have not accepted the Espers as a race
of peace, the Espers are forced to increase their popluation by secretly
tampering with the genetics of unborn humans infants. After the infants are
born, they ..nor their parents are aware of what their infant is. When the
'human' matures to a certain age, a transformation takes place. The body
burns violently and become a mass fire of magick. This is the true form of
an esper and their power excedes any known race that lives in the realm.

You as a character have the opportunity to determine whether you have been 
chosen to become an Esper. There are certain conditions that need to be
followed if you have any chance of becoming one. You must create a human,
and must be of angelic alignment. Your profession must deal soley with magick
so the classes of mage, cleric, and monk are the only classes that will
allow you to transform. And finally, you must have chosen the path of a
player killer. After you have made all the requirements, you gain
experience normally. When you gain a level, a percentage check is made to
see if you 'transform' or not. The check begins when you reach the 25th
level of experience and continues till level 50th. If you meet the race,
class, alignment requirements and roll a 1% out of a 100, your body will
transform and you will become an Esper.

After your transformation, you recieve almost godlike powers when it comes to 
the use of magick. Because you are in fact, Magick itself, the durations of
all your spells casted will be doubled, protective and combat wise. Your
mana costs will be half compared to other magic users. Your attack spells do
double damage, and you will recieve double mana gains per level after trans-
formation. 

An Esper is a unique race, and therefore few mortals will see or grasp its 
powers. Many will never become an Esper, which is a consideration that you 
must take.
~

-1 HOWTODEMON~
As the outer and inner realms combine, the barriers that protect the innocent
from the demonic minions have begun to dissipate. These demons are special
followers of the Lord of Terror himself. Because these beings have no
morals or concerns for the living, they have been repeatedly been held back
from entering the outer realm. However, with the weakening of the barrier,
more and more demons have been escaping and the attempts to stop them have
been all but successful. These demons ravage the lands, murdering and raping
innocent victims of the realm. Because these beasts need some host to
reproduce, they use females that have the ability to bear children to carry
their children. These children are born and raised like humans, for in fact
they are a mirror image of a human. However, the dreaded day arrives in
which a painful tranformation occurs, and the human ..becomes a demon. Their
demon body quickly mutates inside of them and bursts out of its human shell
in a matter of hours. The body is consumed in fire as the transformation 
takes place. Once it has transformed, it has retained all its knowledge as
a human but has transented above mortal living.

The opportunity as a character exists for you to become a minion of the
damned only if certain conditions are followed. The main condition is that
you do have to be of the human race. Your professions would have to deal
with exposure to death and chaos and therefore a warrior, thief, or ninja 
would qualify. You must have chosen the path of a player killer and
finally, you  much be of a satanic alignment, one that already follows the
ways of the demon. When you reach your 25th level of experience, a roll is
made for every level until level 50th. If you keep to the conditions and
make the 1% roll on any level up you have on and after 25th, you will
transform into a demon. 

Because demons were former humans before transformation, they understand
and use to the fullest the weaknesses of the human and other races. Demons 
recieve double hp gains for every level up after transformation. Finally,
the demons have the power to cast the fires of hell upon you.

Because the demons are great in power, many will never become one. Those
that transform have become better than any race that exists in the realm
and therefore gives all races a reason to fear the demons.
~

-1 PK_QUEST~
PKQuests in the realm of `&A``n`&i``m`&e M``U`&D``...

  Here in `&A``n`&i``m`&e M``U`&D`` we hold such events as PKQuest where
mass amounts
of players who wish to participate in killing others can join in. In
a PKQuest you are NOT required to type PK set twice. This is a method
by which you can PK others without becoming a player killer yourself.
In a PKQuest you do not lose EXP or any EQ from your person at all! The
point of a PKQuest if to either: Hold a Major Tournament or basically
have the joy of killing mass opponents. There are no level restrictions
on who you may kill in a PKQuest. Higher levels have the decision of
attacking a lower level if he decides to. Remember PKQuests are for fun
use only, immortals will not tolerate people flooding the channels on 
how unfair it is that you were PKed or how bad your character is or how
bad your class/race is.

To enter a Quest simply type: quest apply 

See also: help <Quest>
~

-1 QUEST~
Quests in the realm of `&A``n`&i``m`&e M``U`&D``...

  Here on `&A``n`&i``m`&e M``U`&D`` we hold a variety of Quests. We range
Quests from:
Trivial Quests, Search and Find Quests, Hack-n-Slash, and to Tournament
Quests. These Quests are for the sole purpose of adding enjoyment to
the game. We, the immortals, try to encourage others to join the Quests
we have out hand for you. Some quests can be very enjoyable and some
can be very nerve wrecking and very hard to deal with at that time. We
encourage that you please have fun when Questing and not flood the public
channels when you have died or have a spell that is hard to remove from 
your character at that particular time. Asking for a restore during a 
Quest is probably something that will occur a lot, but do not expect the
immortal to restore you every time you ask. Restores during a Quest will
be minimal, and will come from time to time. Please have fun when Questing
that is all the immortals ask.

To enter a Quest simply type: quest apply

See also: help <PK_Quest, Quest_Tokens>
~

