-1 AUTOQUEST AUTO_QUEST~
Certain characters in the game will allow you to go on quests to recover an
item or kill another mob. To go on a quest, you must be in the same room with
a questmaster. When you successfully complete a quest, you will receive a
certain number of quest points. These points may be saved up and used to buy
incredible items from the questmaster.
 
The `&AUTOQUEST`` command is used for information about your current quest, to 
request a quest from a questmaster, etc. Commands are as follows:

`&AUTOQUEST POINTS`` `A-`` Gives your current number of quest points. This command 
may be used anywhere.
                      
`&AUTOQUEST INFO `A-`` If you are on a quest, this will remind you who or what 
you are after.
 
`&AUTOQUEST TIME `A-`` Gives the amount of time remaining on your current quest, 
or the amount of time until you can request another quest. This command may 
be used anywhere.

`&AUTOQUEST REQUEST `A-`` Petitions the questmaster to send you on a quest. If 
you accept the quest, you will be given a realtime limit (in minutes) in which 
you must complete the quest. If you are on a quest to kill a creature, when 
you come across that creature you will see a `A[`@TARGET`A]`` notice before it.
This is the creature you are to kill.

`&AUTOQUEST COMPLETE `A-`` Once you have completed your quest and recovered the 
item or killed the mob or whatever, you must return to the questmaster who
sent you on the quest and use this command. If you have successfully 
completed your quest, he will reward you with gold and quest points. Once 
you complete a quest you cannot request another for 30 minutes.

`&AUTOQUEST GIVEUP `A-`` When the quest seems hopeless, you can give up your 
quest by using this command. You do have to wait a length of time before 
you can quest again.

`&AUTOQUEST LIST `A-`` Displays the list of fabulous items for sale by the 
questmaster. These items are not buyable via gold, they must be purchased 
with quest points.  

`&AUTOQUEST BUY <``item`&> `A-`` Purchases an item from the questmaster and deducts
the cost of the item from your quest points.

`&AQSTRING `A-`` Purchases a restring from the QuestMaster. See help AQSTRING.

`&TESTAQSTRING `A-`` Test out AQSTRING before you do it for real! Same syntax as 
AQSTRING!
~

-1 TESTAQSTRING~
Syntax: testaqstring <obj name> "<new name<s>>" "<short desc>" "<long desc>"

The "testaqstring" command allows you to take a piece of equipment in your
inventory and lets you see what it would look like if you used the aqstring
command on it. This is not permenant! It is a tester to use BEFORE you use
aqstring.
~

-1 AQEXAMPLE~
Example for AQstring command`8...``

If you're sketchy on what to type when using AQstring command here's a
little tip on what you should do.
`#1`@)`` Make sure you have all the requirements `6(`^seen on AQstring helpfile`6)``
`#2`@)`` Have ready in notepad of your string, that way you can copy/paste.
`#3`@)`` Keep in mind format`8:``
   Astring <obj name> "<obj keyword(s)>" "<short desc>" "<long desc>"

The Example`8:``
 Astring dagger "dagger power" "a dagger of POWER" "A dagger rests here."

Legend`8:``
`8-``object         = current obj in inventory to be restrung
`8-``new keyword`&(`7s`&)`` = words of item used to get/drop item
`8-``short desc     = words seen when wearing/getting the item
`8-``long desc      = words seen when item is on the ground

`!*``Caution`!*``
 Name field cannot use color code! Nor in any part of your item can
 it be made to have a " character shown. Make sure you know what you're
 doing before you do it! iMM's should not be held accountable for any
 mishaps. Read before you leap.

