-1 CLANSYSTEM~

The new clan system allows players to initate their own clans.
The clans have to be OKed by immortals, so don't get any ideas. ^_^

It works like this:

Player X wants to make a clan, Clan WhatEver.
Players Y and Z want to join.

Player X does a "clan initiate" command to create the clan.
The clan is NOT a real clan at this point and isn't visible to anyone but
X.  Anyway, X proceeds to set the charge to pledge (explained later),
min level to join, how it looks in the who list (long name), etc.  Then, he waits.

Eventually, the Clan IMM with the appropriate command will show up, and decide
whether the clan will be established. If so, it will then become a real clan,
with X as the leader. Or, the Clan IMM can reject the clan, and X LOSES his
payment he paid to create the clan.  To create a clan, you need `!two`` of the following:

`@*`& 250,000`# gold`7.
`@*`& 80`7 RP points (160 to make a Non-PK clan)
`@*`& 3000 autoquest points.`7

`%(`5Note`%)`&: We will be adding more payment methods soon.``  --Batanen

Non-PK clans *MUST* pay using RP points.
Also, Non-PK clans are `&HEAVILY DISCOURAGED`7.  Meaning, if you intend to
create one, there's a `#VERY`7 high chance it will be deleted.  You'd better
have a VERY good backstory, or you're throing away your money. Also, NonPK clans
have *ABSOLUTELY NO CHANCE* to get clan equipment, when those are introduced later.

See help`^ clansys2`7, `^newclans`7, `^clan_upgrade`7, `^clan_upkeep`7,
and  `^clan_rules`7 for more details.
~

-1 CLANSYS2~

`&HELP CLANSYS2``

Anyway, say clan WhatEver gets established.  Now, Y and Z want to join.
This doesn't work like before.  They have to "clan pledge <short name>" to
join.  This pre-checks for min level, PK status, etc.  Somewhat like
writing an app, except you can't lie to it. :P There is also a charge,
between 100 and 10,000 gold, to pledge a clan.  This charge is set by the
leader.

Also, the clan leader can create an "ACL entry" for pledges.  This is to
keep known bad people from pledging, and to make "private" clans, if you
wish.  It works like this:

There are two settings for the "default ACL".  Allow, and deny.
If you set the default to "Allow", everyone NOT on the ACL list can pledge.
If you set the default to "Deny", ONLY those on the ACL list can pledge.
There is a limit to ACL entries, so be careful with them.

Anyway, X can only clan Y and Z after they pledge.  Or he can decide to
delete their pledges.  If they are rejected, they will have to try again.

This system may be revised depending on how well it works.

The old clan system commands are replaced with "clanldr" and "clan".
Type those by themselves for help.

It is extraordinarily important to talk to the Clan IMM before doing a
clan initiate.  Since they are the person who decides on whether the
clan lives or dies, communication is vital.  Send them notes, tells, etc.
in order to be certain your clan will be successful.

Also, read HELP NEWCLANS for notes. 
~

-1 CLAN_UPGRADE~

`&HELP CLAN_UPGRADE`7

For additional fees, clan hall and clan equipment may be added after the
first month's upkeep has been collected on time.  Clan Halls must be purchased
first, before Clan Equipment.  The cost of an upgrade is one of the payment
methods not already used by the creation of a clan, with the possibility of
paying more for additional rooms/items.

Clan Halls will start with 3 rooms; an entrance, and two clan-only safe rooms.
Also, they will be able to clan recall into their clan hall, with the violence
timer off, at no extra fee.  Extra rooms are purchased for 0.5x the cost, with
a limit of 6 clan-only safe rooms.  A clan healer costs 0.25x the cost of a room,
and a clan trainer costs 0.25x the cost of a room. Clan trainers cannot be
purchased by RP Clans.  The upkeep for a clan hall will be 1/10 of the total cost
of the clan hall.  Clan Halls are for clan members ONLY.  Additional rooms/MOBs
can be bought later on.

Clan Equipment starts with 1 item at the base cost. Clan Equipment cannot be
purchased by RP Clans. Additional items cost 0.75x, with a limit of 3 items.
These items will only be available from the Clan Leader, unless a clan shopkeeper
is bought. They of a shopkeeper is 1x the base cost of the clan equipment, is not
part of the clan hall cost. Additional EQ/MOB can be bought later on.


~

-1 CLAN_UPKEEP~

`&HELP CLAN_UPKEEP`7


After the first month of existance, a clan will have to pay an upkeep fee of
1/10 each month of their original payment to the clan.  If clan halls and/or
clan equipment is also purchased, then that is added to the upkeep.

Each clan will have a "safety deposit box" that each clan member will be
able to deposit payments into.  These cannot be returned to you or any
other clan member once deposited.  Every month, the clan IMM will check
the box for payment, and remove the appropriate amount for upkeep.

Initial payments for clan halls and clan equipment will also be handled via
the "safety deposit box."  The Clan Ldr will be able to check on how much
is in the box, to be certain the correct amount is entered in.

If a clan is late on their payments, they may be fined an extra 15% on their
next month's upkeep.  If a clan does not pay their upkeep, or is repeatedly
late on upkeep, it will be taken away, and all clan members will become
clanless.

We will be revising this system, as problems come up with it, please
be patient.


~

-1 CLAN_RULES~

`&HELP CLAN_RULES`7

Due to the major change in the way clans work now, we have a group of rules and
processes that are listed here.  These help clarify any questions people have
about the new clan system.

A person may only have one character in one of the following positions, Clan Initiator,
Clan Leader, Clan Member, and Pledge. Failure to do so will result in punishment,
depending on the crime.

A clan member may request to leave a clan, and may also be kicked out of a clan,
at the clan leader's choice.  A clan member may be rejected when asking to leave
a clan.  Their choices are to recreate, or IMM removal.  If removed by the clan
IMM, they will not be allowed to ever join a clan again with that character.
If the clan leader removes them, they will then be free to pledge any other clan.

If a clan leader decides to step down, the person who is ranked 2nd will then be
made Clan Leader.  If the former leader wishes to choose a new leader for him/herself,
they must indicate that by making that person 2nd ranked.  For this reason,
there should only and always be one person ranked 2nd at one time.

If a clan leader does not logon for more than 18 days, without letting the IMM
staff know ahead of time, they will be removed as leader.  The person who was
ranked 2nd will then be made leader in their stead.  If a member of a clan does
not logon for more than 18 days without letting the Leader know, they will be
allowed to declan the person without their presence.

If there is not someone ranked 2nd in a clan when the clan leader steps down,
a general election within the clan will be done, with the clan members given 48
hours from first notice to vote for their choice for new Leader.  The Clan IMM
will break ties.
